edu.ucla.sspace.vector
Class DenseVector

java.lang.Object
  edu.ucla.sspace.vector.DenseVector
All Implemented Interfaces:
DoubleVector, Vector<Double>, Serializable
public class DenseVector
extends Object
implements DoubleVector, Serializable

A Vector where all values are held in memory. The underlying implementation is simply an array of doubles.

Author:
Keith Stevens
See Also:

DenseVector

public DenseVector(double[] vector)
Create a DenseVector taking the values given by vector. The created vector contains no references to the provided array, so changes to either will not be reflected in the other.

Parameters:
vector - The vector values to start with.

toArray

public double[] toArray()
Returns a double array representing this vector. The returned array will be "safe" in that no changes to the array will be reflected in the vector, and likewise for changes to to the vector. The caller is thus free to modify the returned array.

Specified by:
toArray in interface DoubleVector
Returns:
a double array of this vector.
